title: Employment by economic sector in Iceland 2019
summary: You are viewing a chart of multi-line type with 3 lines denoting Agriculture, Industry, and Services. The y axis indicates the Share of total employment and the x axis indicates Year.
Overall Agriculture, Industry, and Services are roughly constant,  throughout the Year
The ranking of the lines from topmost to botommmost is as follows: 1. Services, 2. Industry, and lastly, 3. Agriculture.
Throughout the period, Services generally had the highest Share of total employment relative to others with an average of 77.39, and it reached its maximum at 2019 with a value of 79.18.
Followed by Industry which ranks as the second topmpost line , with an average of 18.1 Share of total employment,reaching its highest point  at 2009 with a value of 19.5.
The botommost line, Agriculture,  has a mean of 4.52, and peaked at 2010.
Agriculture reported the lowest Share of total employment about 3.69 in Year 2019
